  "title": "WSH Officer",
  "description": "<p>Job Scope & Responsibilites:</p><ul><li><strong>Risk Management:</strong> Identify hazards, conduct risk assessments (RA), and recommend practical control measures to prevent accidents and ill health.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Policy and Program Development:</strong> Supporting the development of WSH policies and programs and implementing the WSH Management System (WSHMS) within the workplace.</li><li><strong>Inspections & Audits:</strong> Perform regular site/workplace inspections, monitor compliance, and conduct internal audits on safety systems.</li><li><strong>Incident Management:</strong> Investigate accidents and near misses, report findings, and ensure effective corrective and preventive actions are implemented.</li><li><strong>Training & Awareness:</strong> Develop and conduct safety briefings, training, and campaigns to raise safety awareness among workers and subcontractors.</li><li><strong>Compliance & Documentation:</strong> Maintain WSH records, submit required reports (e.g., to MOM, NEA), and ensure adherence to legal requirements and company policies.</li><li><strong>System Implementation:</strong> Implement and maintain the company's Environmental, Health, and Safety Management System (EHSMS).</li><li><strong>Liaison and Collaboration:</strong> Working closely with management,\nemployees, contractors and relevant authorities to ensure all safety, health and environmental matters are addressed and all parties comply with the governing law.</li><li><strong>Emergency Preparedness:</strong> Develop emergency plans and\nconduct drills, including firefighting exercises if required. </li></ul><p><br />Job Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in Occupational Safety and Health, Environmental Science, or related discipline.</li><li>At least 2 years of experience as a WSHO and ECO in the Construction sector.</li><li>Registered Workplace Safety and HealthOfficer (WSHO) with MOM.</li><li>Strong understanding of WSH and environmental legislation.</li><li>Excellent communication, organisational, and problem-solving abilities.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and related software tools.</li></ul><p>\n<br />    \n\n</p>",
